<head>CARE FOR</head>
<div type="definition">
<p>SAFEGUARD LOVINGLY.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>愛護 is the general term for taking loving care of someone.</p>
<p>愛惜 focusses on the cherishing care and the desire not to diminish or lose what one cares for.</p>
<p>吝惜 is caring for in which the possessive side of things becomes prominent.</p>
<p>珍惜 focusses on the often aesthetic appreciation of what one cares for, but it is to be noted that the word is also used reflexively as in 珍惜自己.</p>
<p>愛護 focusses on the protective side of the caring for.</p>
<p>呵護 he1hu4 focusses on the neediness of what one cares for.</p>
